		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I'd vote either shadowknight or some flavor of wizard, if you intend on doing any serious PvP activity. <br>  <br> Shadowknights are basically warriors with cool spells, so you can't go wrong there.  My warrior pretty well kicks ass now, but I'd be kicking a lot more ass if I could Dark and Fear at will.  (While you can't fear players, you can fear pets, which is something you'll want to do pretty much anytime you have to fight one.)  Access to invisibility and invisibility to undead gives you a lot of freedom of movement, and feign death is nice when that Lower Guk PvP fight turns into a huge froglok ghoul train.  Be a troll or ogre shadowknight so you have access to Slam. <br>  <br> Wizards are nice in PvP because they don't have a pet.  May sound strange, but in many ways pets are a hinderance in PvP.  They can be rooted, feared, darked, snared, sometimes they go rogue, etc.  Almost every class has a way of easily removing your pet from a battle, particularly at high levels.  A magician without a pet is a lower powered wizard.  Wizards have their limitations, but it's hard to go wrong with raw nuking power. <br>  <br> Necros are good as well, simply because they don't really need their pet to be effective, and they have a couple of good escape spells. <br>  <br>  <br> Pumice stones are bought at your local potion dealer.  They look like a lightstone and cost about 18 plat. <br> 		

